# Data models and relationships

Canonical source: `src/db/schema.ts`. Migrations in `drizzle/`. Runtime dialect: `src/db/dialect.ts`.

## Tables overview

### `platform_users`
Platform identity — both humans (password) and service accounts (API key hash).

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | text PK | UUID |
| `email` | text unique | null for service accounts without email |
| `password_hash` | text | null for service accounts |
| `principal_kind` | text NN | `human` or `service` |
| `role` | text NN | `seller`, `payer`, `admin`, `risk_analyst`, `risk_analyst_agent` |
| `status` | text NN | `active` (default) |
| `service_api_key_hash` | text | null for humans |
| `created_at_ms` / `updated_at_ms` | text NN | epoch ms as string |

Index: `platform_users_role_idx` on `role`.

---

### `receivables`
Core business entity. Seller submits; payer confirms; system settles.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | text PK | UUID |
| `seller_user_id` | text NN → `platform_users.id` | Creator |
| `payer_user_id` | text NN → `platform_users.id` | Counterpart; immutable after creation |
| `status` | text NN | See `receivable-workflows` rule for state machine |
| `value` | text NN | Original requested value |
| `proposed_value` | text | Set by risk when moving to `offer` |
| `receivable_md` | text | Optional markdown description from seller |
| `created_at_ms` / `updated_at_ms` | text NN | epoch ms as string; `created_at_ms` immutable |

Indexes: `seller_user_id`, `payer_user_id`, `status`.

